The paper deals with the problem of learning from multiple sources, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the effects of adversarial perturbations on the learning process, which is a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper presents a generalization bound, which is a statistical learning theory concept and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of cooperative learning, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
